<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-10-04T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-10-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="917" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d917">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 422.11G93/936</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Hartman</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Quito</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-10-04">
                                    <hi rend="italic">October 4, 1917</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Last Friday Congress passed a resolution repealing the resolution of
                            October last which authorized a commission to adjust differences between
                            Ecuador and Guayaquil and Quito Railway Company. The resolution also
                            declared in full force the resolution of October 1915, which instructed
                            fiscal attorney to bring suit against railway company. Full report by
                            mail.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hartman</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>